<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="180" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,151,177]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marchenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[476,549,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Halolaelapidae" genus="Halozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aesopi">
<emphasis box="[476,549,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">aesopi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
named after the ancient Greek fabulist Aesop.Aesop became famous for writing fables about different animals and according to legend he was a humpback.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="180" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,223,249]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Remarks</emphasis>
. Dorsal idiosoma of 
<taxonomicName authority="Marchenko, 2021" authorityName="Marchenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[553,765,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Halolaelapidae" genus="Halozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="29" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aesopi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[553,765,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Halozercon aesopi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[775,841,223,249]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[775,841,223,249]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from other species of genus by hump in the central part of opisthonotum and very long plumose marginal setae on very high bases.All dorsal pore-like structures enlarged. Opisthonotal lateral setae are few, about six. In vertex seta 
<emphasis box="[914,939,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">z1</emphasis>
indistinct (absent). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krefft" authorityYear="1871" box="[1159,1301,295,321]" class="Chromadorea" family="Gnathostomatidae" genus="Gnathosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="177" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">Gnathosoma</taxonomicName>
with pair of relief arcs in the form of a crescent located meridionally near the 
<emphasis box="[875,901,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">pc</emphasis>
setae. Pretarsus of legs II–IV with enlarged pair of median pulvillus with rounded top significantly rises above the claws and paradactyls.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
